edition of the opinions of the
present SKtB' staff leaves the
board open for further criticism. The refused to became
the present editor can be inter
posted as a structure of the
quality of the 5&3. The start is
naturally indignant over this indirect attack, which is ulie
called-for.
Many on the staff reel re
instant to continue working for
the new editor ill light of this
criticism. Should the new Edl'
for find herself without a
trained start next year, a ma
for problem, for the 53:3 and
for the entire college, will develop.
Another interesting outcome
